{
  "texts": [
    "The physician then classified wound features and the healing phase of the DFU and provided a confidence percentage of the classification as outlined on the CRF.",
    "Images and forms were marked with timestamps to avoid misplacements.",
    "The image capture and CRF fillings were repeated for each patient at the follow-up appointments until the wound was classified as healed by the clinician or the participant withdrew from the study.",
    "All images were taken to exclude faces and identifiable information; however, the researchers took special considerations to blur any recognizable objects or aspects if included in the images.",
    "Deep learning evaluation on the Zivot datasetThe efficacy and value of this dataset were demonstrated in the wound detection aspect of DL."
  ]
}